'From Squeak3.7beta of ''1 April 2004'' [latest update: #5972] on 17 July 2004 at 1:49:21 am'!"Change Set:		advanceToGammaOr38-dewDate:			17 July 2004Author:			Doug WayThis is the last update for version 3.7beta.  In its postscript is an executable statement that will set the version forward to either 3.7gamma or 3.8alpha, at user option."!"Postscript:Offer the chance to advance the version number."(self confirm: 'There are no further updates for Squeak 3.7beta.Do you wish to advance to version 3.8alpha?[Yes] Your system will be marked as 3.8alpha, and you willsubsequently receive ''test pilot'' updates for 3.8.[No] Your system will be marked as 3.7gamma, allowing youto receive only final fixes for the 3.7 stable release.[Neither] You may choose No, and immediately quit without saving,allowing you to make a backup copy before adopting this change.DO YOU WANT TO ADVANCE to Version 3.8alpha now?')	ifTrue: [SystemVersion newVersion: 'Squeak3.8alpha'.			SystemVersion current date: '17 July 2004'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.8alpha imageand retrieve updates again for 3.8alpha and beyond.']	ifFalse: [SystemVersion current version: 'Squeak3.7gamma'; date: '17 July 2004'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.7gamma imageand retrieve updates again for any final fixes to 3.7.- - - - -(If you quit without saving now, your image will revert to3.7beta without any of the updates you just loaded)'].!